ZH: 他们卑躬屈膝地请求老板给予更多的机会。
EN: They humbly begged the boss for more opportunities.

ZH: 你不必卑躬屈膝地向任何人乞求尊重。
EN: You don't have to grovel to anyone for respect.

ZH: 在这个国家，人们不需要卑躬屈膝地向权势低头。
EN: In this country, people don't need to bow down to power.

ZH: 我的父母教育我要以正直的态度面对困境，而不是卑躬屈膝。
EN: My parents taught me to face challenges with honesty, not to grovel.

ZH: 尽管他卑躬屈膝地请求原谅，她还是拒绝了他。
EN: Despite his groveling for forgiveness, she still refused him.

ZH: 当面对困难时，他没有卑躬屈膝，而是勇敢地直面挑战。
EN: When faced with difficulties, he didn't grovel, but bravely faced the challenge.

ZH: 在这个家庭里，没有一个人会卑躬屈膝地向别人低头。
EN: In this family, no one will grovel to others.

ZH: 尽管他被解雇了，他并没有卑躬屈膝地求情。
EN: Despite being fired, he did not grovel for mercy.

ZH: 在这种情况下，你不需要卑躬屈膝地请求帮助。
EN: In this situation, you don't need to grovel for help.

ZH: 他坚决不会卑躬屈膝地接受这种不公平的待遇。
EN: He would never grovel to accept such unfair treatment.

ZH: 他并不后悔卑躬屈膝地请求帮助。
EN: He does not regret groveling for help.

ZH: 即使卑躬屈膝也没有用，他还是试图。
EN: Even though groveling was useless, he still tried.

ZH: 我不会卑躬屈膝地请求别人的仁慈。
EN: I will not grovel for someone's mercy.

ZH: 请你别再卑躬屈膝地请求我的原谅。
EN: Please stop groveling for my forgiveness.

ZH: 虽然他不得不卑躬屈膝地向对方低头，但内心并没有放弃自尊。
EN: Although he had to grovel to bow to the other person, he did not give up his self-esteem.

ZH: 当她卑躬屈膝请求帮助时，没有人给她指出实际的解决方案。
EN: When she groveled for help, no one pointed out the actual solution to her.

ZH: 在那种情况下，他不会卑躬屈膝地请求任何帮助。
EN: In that situation, he will not grovel for any help.

ZH: 尽管他卑躬屈膝地向对方低头，但内心却并不服从。
EN: Although he groveled and bowed down to the other person, his heart did not submit.

ZH: 当他意识到自己不应该不亮不净的时候，他开始卑躬屈膝地请求原谅。
EN: When he realized that he should not be wrong, he began to grovel for forgiveness.

ZH: 哪怕再困难，我也不会卑躬屈膝地向他低头。
EN: No matter how difficult it is, I will not grovel to bow to him.
